=== Readme ===

********** INSTALL **********
Note: this project has been developped in Eclipse.

_____ Eclipse _____
- Install Maven in Eclipse (this helps to manage the dependencies of the libraries).

- Add the following lines in the file pom.xml after </build> in order to install Selenium (Firefox Driver) and Browsermob:
  <dependencies>
   <dependency>
    <groupId>org.seleniumhq.selenium</groupId>
    <artifactId>selenium-firefox-driver</artifactId>
    <version>2.40.0</version>
   </dependency>
   <dependency>
    <groupId>net.lightbody.bmp</groupId>
    <artifactId>browsermob-proxy</artifactId>
    <version>2.0-beta-9</version>
   </dependency>
  </dependencies>

- Download HarLib (from https://sites.google.com/site/frogthinkerorg/projects/harlib) and add harlib-nodoc-xxx.jar to the classpath (Jackson is already included with the other libs).
- Download Apache Commons CLI (from http://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-cli/) and add commons-cli-xx.jar to the classpath.

How to add a library in Eclipse:
> Right click on the project => Properties.
> Select "Java Build Path" on the left => click on the "Libraries" tab => click on "Add External JARs..." and select the jar files downloaded before.

_____ Firefox _____
- create a new profile in Firefox:
  => run firefox -P
- add the certificate (cybervillainsCA.cer) to the profile in Firefox (2 methods):
  A) go to "Edit" => "Preferences" => "Advanced" tab => "Certificates" subtab and install the certificate
  B) find your profile in /home/XXX/.mozilla and replace the file "cert8.db" with the one provided here
- install Firebug: https://getfirebug.com/
- install NetExport: https://getfirebug.com/wiki/index.php/Firebug_Extensions#NetExport


********** RUN **********
Launch "java -jar Code.jar" followed by the arguments.
Note: launch "java -jar Code.jar -h" to get help.
